Introduction [id=fba3_intro_section]
------------
psych_sba_sidebar6 -> fba3_introduction

Lin: So how did the intervention go with your roommate?

Annie: Thanks for asking! My roommate read our intervention plan. She tracked his progress in her journal. Over the past 2 weeks, she babysat 5 times. He went to bed on time 2 of the 5 occasions. On one of those occasions where he did not go to bed on time, she noted that she did not exactly follow our plan. In fact, the escape behaviors seem to have gotten worse over time!

JJ: That doesn't sound good at all.

Progress Monitoring [id=fba3_progress_section]
-------------------
psych_sba_sidebar6 -> fba3_progress_graph_1

Lin: Let's talk to our professor to find more resources to help improve the plan.

Annie: We showed the graph to the professor and explained that the roommate admitted she did not follow all of the consequence strategies.

Lianne: Looks like you need to improve on implementation fidelity.

Implementation Fidelity [id=fba3_fidelity_section]
------------------------
psych_sba_sidebar6 -> fba3_fidelity_info

Lin: Okay, our professor gave us lots of good resources. Intervention fidelity refers to how accurately and consistently a behavior plan is implemented as it was designed.

JJ: In other words, was Annie's roommate doing what our plan says they should do?

psych_sba_sidebar6 -> fba3_fidelity_tabs

Annie: Now we're getting somewhere! Let me text my roommate to see exactly where things went wrong...

Fidelity Check [id=fba3_fidelity_check_section]
---------------
psych_sba_sidebar6 -> fba3_fidelity_check

Annie: My roommate got back to me! She said that sometimes she forgets to do the warning countdown and timer, she forgets the small bedtime reward, and often falls into negotiating or arguing when he whines for extended time.

--- wait @fba3_fidelity_choice.submitCount > 0 ---

